{"type":"message","id":"20a3137f","parentId":"63c5f03b","timestamp":"2026-07-03T08:14:40.907Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_abab026abff14f1682923b94","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Content Strategy — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Business Goal\n\nGrow personal brand with focus on AI Autonomous Organizations and AI Agents. Position as a multi-company operator building at the intersection of AI and business transformation.\n\n## Posting Cadence\n\n- **Frequency:** 2-3 times per day\n- **Preferred schedule:** Every day\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n*(Carried from brand voice profile)*\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Key Messages\n\n*(The beliefs and positions every post should reinforce)*\n1. AI can be affordable and accessible — even for small businesses\n2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n3. Every company will become AI-first — the question is when, not if\n\n## Target Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who you are writing for — each post should speak to at least one)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) — Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency — Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB — Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Topics to Avoid\n\n(none — open to all topics)\n\n## Upcoming Campaigns\n\n- **Benchgen.com launch** — Benchmarking product (mention organically, not primary focus)\n- **UBOS.tech improvements** — AI Agent Orchestration Platform (mention organically, not primary focus)\n\n## Strategic Positioning\n\nPersonal brand > individual company promotion. Building reputation as an AI thought leader and multi-company operator. Content should position Andrii as the voice on AI Autonomous Organizations, not just a founder pushing products.\n\n## Pillar Balance Target\n\nWith 2-3 posts/day, aim for roughly equal coverage across all 3 pillars each week. Mix formats: thought leadership, tactical insights, personal stories, news reactions. Prioritize AI Agents and Autonomous Organizations angles across all pillars.\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Strategy created\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783066480905}}
