"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5bcee686691a4560ae0af6dc","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783145644084,"responseId":"rqRIarTYBv6B_NUPxo2uoQY"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ce1f4db","parentId":"4b93b7a3","timestamp":"2026-07-04T06:14:15.083Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5fffeae69e764735a6805bfa","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/bin/sh: 7: Syntax error: \")\" unexpected\n\n(Command exited with code 2)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":2,"durationMs":10,"aggregated":"/usr/bin/sh: 7: Syntax error: \")\" unexpected\n\n(Command exited with code 2)","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":true,"timestamp":1783145655081}}
{"type":"message","id":"65908537","parentId":"4ce1f4db","timestamp":"2026-07-04T06:14:15.087Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d470ef8431024c7888e21ea5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783145655086}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2282fe2","parentId":"65908537","timestamp":"2026-07-04T06:14:15.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5bcee686691a4560ae0af6dc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Content Strategy — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-06-25\n\n## Business Goal\n\nGrow personal brand with focus on AI Autonomous Organizations and AI Agents. Position as a multi-company operator building at the intersection of AI and business transformation.\n\n## Posting Cadence\n\n- **Frequency:** 2-3 times per day\n- **Preferred schedule:** Every day\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n*(Carried from brand voice profile)*\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Key Messages\n\n*(The beliefs and positions every post should reinforce)*\n1. AI can be affordable and accessible — even for small businesses\n2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n3. Every company will become AI-first — the question is when, not if\n\n## Target Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who you are writing for — each post should speak to at least one)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) — Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency — Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB — Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Topics to Avoid\n\n(none — open to all topics)\n\n## Upcoming Campaigns\n\n- **Benchgen.com launch** — Benchmarking product (mention organically, not primary focus)\n- **UBOS.tech improvements** — AI Agent Orchestration Platform (mention organically, not primary focus)\n\n## Strategic Positioning\n\nPersonal brand > individual company promotion. Building reputation as an AI thought leader and multi-company operator. Content should position Andrii as the voice on AI Autonomous Organizations, not just a founder pushing products.\n\n## Pillar Balance Target\n\nWith 2-3 posts/day, aim for roughly equal coverage across all 3 pillars each week. Mix formats: thought leadership, tactical insights, personal stories, news reactions. Prioritize AI Agents and Autonomous Organizations angles across all pillars.\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Strategy created\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783145655090}}
