{"type":"message","id":"611a699a","parentId":"3cde3c47","timestamp":"2026-07-04T06:15:07.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1a895f0df954492295e3b7d8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending\"\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-04\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗿.\n\nNot replacing it. Eating it.\n\nThe COO who spends 60% of their time on coordination, status checks, and \"just checking in\" emails? That's the layer AI agents are automating right now.\n\nHere's what's actually happening:\n\nCompanies aren't firing managers. They're giving them AI agents that handle the coordination work. The managers who survive are the ones who shift from \"managing processes\" to \"making decisions.\"\n\nThe ones who don't? They become the process.\n\nIf your job is mostly routing information between humans, you have 18-24 months to reinvent yourself. Not because AI is coming — because it's already here.\n\nWhat's one thing you're doing this week that an AI agent could do instead?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #FutureOfWork #Leadership #Innovation\nDRAFT_EOF\n\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-04\nn: 2\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗳𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗯𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\n\nYou've got the best product in your category. Congratulations.\n\nNo one knows.\n\nMeanwhile, your competitor with the \"good enough\" product is on every podcast, every newsletter, every LinkedIn feed. They're winning because they showed up.\n\nHere's the uncomfortable truth:\n\nBuilding something great is the baseline. If you're not distributing, you're not building a business — you're building a hobby.\n\nThe founders who win aren't the ones with the perfect product. They're the ones who ship, talk about it, ship again, and keep talking.\n\nWhat's one distribution channel you've been avoiding because it feels \"not ready yet\"?\n\n#Startups #Entrepreneurship #Distribution #Growth #FounderLife\nDRAFT_EOF\n\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-04\nn: 3\npillar: Personal development & mindset\nsource: evergreen\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗯𝘂𝗿𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝗼𝘂𝘁. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗲𝗱.\n\nBig difference.\n\nBurnout needs rest. Boredom needs change.\n\nIf you're exhausted but can't sleep, that's burnout. Take a break.\n\nIf you're tired but the moment you start something new you feel alive, that's boredom. You've been doing the same thing too long. Your brain is screaming for novelty.\n\nMost people mistake boredom for burnout. They rest. They come back. They're still bored. So they rest more. The cycle repeats.\n\nThe fix isn't less work. It's different work.\n\nSame skills, new context. Same expertise, new problem. Same you, new challenge.\n\nWhen was the last time you felt genuinely excited about what you were working on?\n\n#Mindset #Growth #Career #PersonalDevelopment #Energy\nDRAFT_EOF\n\ntouch \"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\n\necho \"DRAFTS_CREATED=3\"\nls -la \"$PENDING_DIR/\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending\\\"\\nmkdir -p \\\"$PENDING_DIR\\\"\\n\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-04\\nn: 1\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗿.\\n\\nNot replacing it. Eating it.\\n\\nThe COO who spends 60% of their time on coordination, status checks, and \\\"just checking in\\\" emails? That's the layer AI agents are automating right now.\\n\\nHere's what's actually happening:\\n\\nCompanies aren't firing managers. They're giving them AI agents that handle the coordination work. The managers who survive are the ones who shift from \\\"managing processes\\\" to \\\"making decisions.\\\"\\n\\nThe ones who don't? They become the process.\\n\\nIf your job is mostly routing information between humans, you have 18-24 months to reinvent yourself. Not because AI is coming — because it's already here.\\n\\nWhat's one thing you're doing this week that an AI agent could do instead?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #FutureOfWork #Leadership #Innovation\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-04\\nn: 2\\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗳𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗺𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗯𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\\n\\nYou've got the best product in your category. Congratulations.\\n\\nNo one knows.\\n\\nMeanwhile, your competitor with the \\\"good enough\\\" product is on every podcast, every newsletter, every LinkedIn feed. They're winning because they showed up.\\n\\nHere's the uncomfortable truth:\\n\\nBuilding something great is the baseline. If you're not distributing, you're not building a business — you're building a hobby.\\n\\nThe founders who win aren't the ones with the perfect product. They're the ones who ship, talk about it, ship again, and keep talking.\\n\\nWhat's one distribution channel you've been avoiding because it feels \\\"not ready yet\\\"?\\n\\n#Startups #Entrepreneurship #Distribution #Growth #FounderLife\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-04\\nn: 3\\npillar: Personal development & mindset\\nsource: evergreen\\nsource_date: 2026-07-04\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗯𝘂𝗿𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝗼𝘂𝘁. 𝗬𝗼𝘂'𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗲𝗱.\\n\\nBig difference.\\n\\nBurnout needs rest. Boredom needs change.\\n\\nIf you're exhausted but can't sleep, that's burnout. Take a break.\\n\\nIf you're tired but the moment you start something new you feel alive, that's boredom. You've been doing the same thing too long. Your brain is screaming for novelty.\\n\\nMost people mistake boredom for burnout. They rest. They come back. They're still bored. So they rest more. The cycle repeats.\\n\\nThe fix isn't less work. It's different work.\\n\\nSame skills, new context. Same expertise, new problem. Same you, new challenge.\\n\\nWhen was the last time you felt genuinely excited about what you were working on?\\n\\n#Mindset #Growth #Career #PersonalDevelopment #Energy\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\ntouch \\\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"DRAFTS_CREATED=3\\\"\\nls -la \\\"$PENDING_DIR/\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783145682373,"responseId":"06RIauiPK5DzzeYP2b28qAQ"}}
